Name: Sara Ng Hui Min¶

I will be working on the Airfoil Noise Dataset (UCI Machine Learning Repository: Airfoil Self-Noise Data Set), exploring it and building a model to evaluate the performance of the various features on the impact of the noise pressure level.

The data set used comprises of different size NACA 0012 airfoils at various wind tunnel speeds and angles of attack. The span of the airfoil and the observer position were the same in all of the experiments.

Attribute Info:¶

This problem has the following inputs:

  1. Frequency, in Hertz.
  2. Angle of attack, in degrees.
  3. Chord length, in meters.
  4. Free-stream velocity, in meters per second.
  5. Suction side displacement thickness, in meters.

The only output is:

  1. Scaled sound pressure level, in decibels.

R shows how well the data fit the regression model. The higher the R, the better the model fits the data. The Root mean squared error (RMSE) tells how concentrated the data is around the line of best fit. The lower the value, the better the model.

Based on the results from Case 1, the model has an accuracy score of about 0.5 and a RMSE score of about 0.73. This indicates that linear regression is not that suitable to be used in the model.

In [20]:
# training linear regression model with k-fold cross-validation
kf = KFold(n_splits=10, random_state=100, shuffle=True)  # 10-fold cross validation

kfold_r2 = []     # storing the r2 for each fold
kfold_rmse = []   # storing the rmse for each fold

lr = LinearRegression()

X_kf = pd.DataFrame(X)
y_kf = pd.DataFrame(y)

for train_index, test_index in kf.split(X_kf):
    X_train, X_test = X_kf.iloc[train_index], X_kf.iloc[test_index]
    y_train, y_test = y_kf.iloc[train_index], y_kf.iloc[test_index]
    
    mod = lr.fit(X_train, y_train)
    y_pred = lr.predict(X_test)
    
    kf_acc = r2_score(y_test, y_pred)
    kf_RMSE = mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred, squared=False)
    kfold_r2.append(kf_acc)
    kfold_rmse.append(kf_RMSE)

print("The R2 score for each fold is:\n", kfold_r2, "\n")
print("The RSME for each fold is:\n", kfold_rmse, "\n")
print("*********************************************")
print(f"Overall R2 score: {np.mean(kfold_r2)}")
print(f"Overall RMSE score: {np.mean(kfold_rmse)}")

In [22]:
# evaluating the different models 
lr = LinearRegression()
r = Ridge()
dt = DecisionTreeRegressor(random_state=100)
svr = SVR(kernel = 'rbf')

print("R2 score and RMSE for selected features:\n")

models = [lr, r, dt, svr]
r2_all = []     # storing the r2 for each fold
rmse_all = []   # storing the rmse for each fold

i = 1
for mod in models: 
    mod.fit(X_train1, y_train1.ravel())
    y_pred = mod.predict(X_test1)
    acc = r2_score(y_test1, y_pred)
    rmse = mean_squared_error(y_test1, y_pred, squared=False)
    r2_all.append(acc)
    rmse_all.append(rmse)
    
    print(f"{i}. {mod}:")
    print(f"R2 score for {mod}: {acc}")
    print(f"RMSE score for {mod}: {rmse} \n")
    print("*************************************\n")
    i+=1
